rlVizLib.utilities
Class TaskSpecDelegate

java.lang.Object
  rlVizLib.utilities.TaskSpecDelegate
Deprecated. We're now goign to use task spec stuff from the RLGlue Java Codec. 

public abstract class TaskSpecDelegate
extends java.lang.Object

Here's the trick. We'll write this class to be the go-to class, that the task spec object will talk to. We'll extend this class over time, adding more stuff to it, but we'll be careful such that we don't need to *ever* change existing subclasses. Lets pretend that's what I mean.

mradkie
